&lt;div class="admonition note"&gt;
&lt;p class="admonition-title"&gt;Note&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Redis uses port 6379 as the default, which is where those ports in the command come from.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;section id="install"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Install&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a id="rest_code_280ec464c5f742dfa73f3567d034ba3c-1" name="rest_code_280ec464c5f742dfa73f3567d034ba3c-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;docker pull redis
&lt;a id="rest_code_280ec464c5f742dfa73f3567d034ba3c-2" name="rest_code_280ec464c5f742dfa73f3567d034ba3c-2"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;docker run -d -p &lt;span class="m"&gt;6379&lt;/span&gt;:6379 --name redis redis
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section id="use-it-with-python-redis"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Use it with python-redis&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;pre class="code python"&gt;&lt;a id="rest_code_ea1bcc3cbf364ccdb19fd7e5272b34f0-1" name="rest_code_ea1bcc3cbf364ccdb19fd7e5272b34f0-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nn"&gt;redis&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a id="rest_code_ea1bcc3cbf364ccdb19fd7e5272b34f0-2" name="rest_code_ea1bcc3cbf364ccdb19fd7e5272b34f0-2"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;client&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;redis&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Redis&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;"localhost"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;6379&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a id="rest_code_ea1bcc3cbf364ccdb19fd7e5272b34f0-3" name="rest_code_ea1bcc3cbf364ccdb19fd7e5272b34f0-3"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;client&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;keys&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code class="docutils literal"&gt;client.keys()&lt;/code&gt; is a double-check. The &lt;code class="docutils literal"&gt;client&lt;/code&gt; object won't actually try to connect to the server until you call it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;</description><category>docker</category><category>how-to</category><category>redis</category><guid>https://necromuralist.github.io/posts/running-redis-in-docker/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 20 Jun 2016 03:25:26 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>